Properties.Description:
A breed of cattle, which is a stock of animals within a species having a distinctive appearance and typically having been developed by deliberate selection.

Ex: 
(Beef)
- Black Angus
- Charolais
- Hereford
- Simmental
- Red Angus
- Texas Longhorn
- Gelbvieh
- Holstein
- Limousin
- Highlands

(Dairy)
- Holstein
- Brown Swiss
- Guernsey
- Ayrshire
- Jersey
- Red and White 
- Milking Shorthorn.
